# Prototype the Local Graph and Backlinks Panel

## Step

The Roam/Logseq payoff: loop and observation pages get backlinks ("what points here") and a small local-graph panel — 1–2 hops out from the current node, rendered from `graph.json` as quiet inline SVG. Tufte rules: no physics-simulation toy, no zooming hairball; a legible, static neighborhood diagram that answers "what is this connected to and why".

Prototype it on the live wiki and let Joel navigate by graph for a few days. Resolved when he keeps it — or the panel dies and the answer records why.

**Status 2026-07-12**: live (wiki `dab3193`) — backlinks ("What points here") + 1–2 hop neighborhood SVG on loop/observation pages, deterministic radial layout, truncation stated. Note: loops mostly have out-edges only, so backlinks shine on observation pages. Awaiting Joel's navigate-and-keep verdict at https://brain.joelclaw.com.
